 Workstyle, a new serviced office and co-working space, has launched in Westlands, Nairobi. ALSO READ:

Don’t be fooled by money myths Grace Wairimu, Workstyle’s general manager, said most commercial buildings in prime locations are targeted at large companies, yet most businesses have a staff count of under 10. Workstyle is ideal for businesses seeking flexible workspace and is targeting tech and business start-ups, event organisers and young high growth businesses with several staff members in need of a shared working space.